name: designates
explanatoryNote: This property is intended to cover assigning a job or role to someone, selecting or designating someone to fill an office or a position, and fixing or setting by authority or by mutual agreement.
label: designates
definition: appoints someone officially

name: isCausedBy
label: is caused by
definition: is the relationship between an event (the effect) and a second event (the cause), where the first event is understood as a consequence of the second; also, the relationship between a set of factors (causes) and a phenomenon (the effect)

name: exchanges
label: exchanges
definition: gives something in return something else

name: hasDesignation
definition: relates an individual or organization to a position, role, or other designation
label: has designation

name: isEvaluatedBy
definition: is ascertained or determined by
label: is evaluated by

name: isGeneratedBy
label: is generated by
definition: identifies some party or something that produces something via some equation, logic, or rules

name: isDesignatedBy
label: is designated by
definition: indicates the party that has assigned or appointed someone to an office or position

name: generates
label: generates
definition: produces through the application of one or more mathematical or logical steps or rules

name: hasTag
definition: combination of alphanumeric characters corresponding to a label for something
label: has tag

name: isIssuedBy
label: is issued by
definition: indicates a functional entity or party responsible for circulating, distributing, or publishing something

name: isManagedBy
label: is managed by
definition: relates something to another thing that has some role in directing its affairs
explanatoryNote: The target or range of this property should be read as always being some kind of 'relative thing', that is a thing defined in some context. Generally this will be a 'party in role'. This property is not intended to be used to relate a thing to some independent thing which it is managed by, only to something in the role of being that which manages it.

name: isConferredBy
explanatoryNote: This property should be read as describing some legal power or duty, some commitment or some social construct being conferred as a result of some social construct such as an agreement or some legal authority. These concepts, which would describe the kind of thing of which this is a property, and the kinds of thing in terms of which this property is framed, are outside the scope of this model and so are not shown.
label: is conferred by
definition: a relationship between a right or obligation and the vehicle, such as an agreement or contract, that vests (or confers) said right or obligation

name: isApplicableIn
explanatoryNote: The context may include the setting in which something is defined, expressed, or represented.

name: isControlledBy
definition: is influenced, managed, or directed by
label: is controlled by

name: hasLegalName
definition: specifies the name used to refer to a party in legal communications
label: has legal name

name: isProvidedBy
definition: is made available by
explanatoryNote: The target or range of this property should be read as always being some kind of 'relative thing', that is a thing defined in some context. Generally this will be a 'party in role'. This property is not intended to be used to relate a thing to some independent thing which it is provided by, only to something in the role of being that which provides it.
label: is provided by

name: manages
label: manages
definition: relates a party to something that it directs in some way

name: hasFormalName
definition: indicates a name by which something is known for some official purpose or context, or which is structured in some way such as to always follow the same format regardless of usage
label: has formal name

name: issues
definition: officially makes something available
label: issues

name: confers
explanatoryNote: This property should be read as describing the conferral of some legal power or duty, some commitment or some social construct, and is a property of some social construct such as an agreement or some legal authority. These concepts, which would describe the kind of thing of which this is a property, and the kinds of thing in terms of which this property is framed, are outside the scope of this mode land so are not shown.
definition: grants or bestows by virtue of some authority
label: confers

name: isExemplifiedBy
label: is exemplified by
definition: is made concrete or is realized by

name: controls
label: controls
definition: exercises authority or influence over

name: wasFormerlyKnownAs
definition: indicates a name by which something was known in the past
label: was formerly known as

name: causes
label: causes
definition: relationship between an event or set of events or factors (the cause) and a second event, phenomenon, situation, or result (the effect), where the second event or outcome is understood as a consequence of the first

name: produces
label: produces
definition: creates through a fabrication, manufacturing or production process

name: mandates
definition: relates something to a commitment, contract, law, obligation, requirement, regulation, or similar concept that requires it
label: mandates

name: isProducedBy
label: is produced by
definition: identifies the producer that fabricates, manufactures or otherwise creates something through some production process

name: Referent
label: referent
definition: something that another concept stands for, exemplifies, symbolizes, or otherwise mentions

name: embodies
label: embodies
definition: is an expression of, gives a tangible or visible form to (an idea, quality, or feeling), makes concrete and perceptible

name: holds
definition: is the relationship between a party and something it possesses, or over which it exercises some ownership or control or has at its discretion the ability to dispose of it as it sees fit
label: holds

name: isMandatedBy
definition: relates a responsibility, capacity, or action to that which requires it
label: is mandated by

name: governs
label: governs
definition: has and exercises authority over, regulates

name: evaluates
definition: assesses the nature, quality, or ability of someone or something
label: evaluates

name: hasTextualName
definition: associates a string-valued name, reference name, or appellation with something
label: has textual name

name: hasAlias
definition: indicates an alternate name of by which something is known
label: has alias

name: isHeldBy
label: is held by
definition: indicates the party that possesses and has at least partial control of something, regardless of ownership

name: isGovernedBy
label: is governed by
definition: relates a contract, agreement, jurisdiction, or other legal construct and the regulation, policy, procedure, or legal person that regulates or oversees (governs) it
explanatoryNote: This property should be read as being the property of some thing and as referring to a logical union of social construct (in the informative abstractions ontology) and legal person.

name: involves
definition: (of a situation or event) includes (something) as a necessary part or result
label: involves

name: hasCommonName
definition: indicates a name by which something is frequently referred, without reference to any formal usage or structure
label: has common name

name: exemplifies
definition: is a concrete realization or example of
label: exemplifies

name: provides
definition: makes something available
label: provides

name: isSignifiedBy
explanatoryNote: 'is signified by' relates a concept to some textual or other symbol which is intended to convey the sense of that concept or to some form of words that sets out the meaning of that concept.
